{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketRef"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is the platform independent base upon which the higher level"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network primitives are based. Applications are not typically meant to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use it directly, but rather through classes like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketService"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":". However there may be cases where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direct use of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is useful."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" implements the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"type":"text","text":" interface, so if it is manually constructed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" you must call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" and check the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results before using the object. This is done automatically in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_new_from_fd()"},{"type":"text","text":", so these functions can return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sockets operate in two general modes, blocking or non-blocking. When"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in blocking mode all operations (which donâ€™t take an explicit blocking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter) block until the requested operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is finished or there is an error. In non-blocking mode all calls that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would block return immediately with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":" error."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To know when a call would successfully run you can call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_condition_check()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_condition_wait()"},{"type":"text","text":". You can also use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_create_source()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attach it to a [MainContext](\/\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext to get callbacks when I\/O is possible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note that all sockets are always set to non blocking mode in the system, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"blocking mode is emulated in GSocket."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When working in non-blocking mode applications should always be able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handle getting a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":" error even when some other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function said that I\/O was possible. This can easily happen in case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a race condition in the application, but it can also happen for other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reasons. For instance, on Windows a socket is always seen as writable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"until a write returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSockets"},{"type":"text","text":" can be either connection oriented or datagram based."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For connection oriented types you must first establish a connection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"either connecting to an address or accepting a connection from another"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"address. For connectionless socket types the target\/source address is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified or received in each I\/O operation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All socket file descriptors are set to be close-on-exec."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that creating a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" causes the signal "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGPIPE"},{"type":"text","text":" to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ignored for the remainder of the program. If you are writing a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"command-line utility that uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":", you may need to take into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"account the fact that your program will not automatically be killed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if it tries to write to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stdout"},{"type":"text","text":" after it has been closed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like most other APIs in GLib, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is not inherently thread safe. To use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" concurrently from multiple threads, you must implement your own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"locking."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socketref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DatagramBasedProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject14GWeakCapturingP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketRef"}],"title":"SocketRef","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:3GIO9SocketRefV","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketRef"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef\/init(_:)-12wgv","doc